	<p>
		The goal of this workshop is to connect the error bound for Taylor polynomial approximations to an error bound for a numerical integration method. Specifically, we will work through proving the error bound <me>\left|\int_{a}^{b} f(x)\,dx - \mbox{MID}(n)\right|\leq \frac{M(b-a)^3}{24n^2}</me> when <m>|f''(x)|\leq M</m> for <m>a\leq x\leq b</m>.
