	<p>
		Before we begin the questions, we first need to set up the notation for all of the questions. We will have a function <m>f(x)</m> that is defined and twice differentiable for <m>a\leq x\leq b</m>. We suppose that <m>|f''(x)|\leq M</m> for all <m>a\leq x\leq b</m>. The interval <m>[a,b]</m> is subdivided into <m>n</m> intervals of equal length <m>\Delta x = \frac{b-a}{n}</m>. The endpoints of each sub-interval are labeled as follows: <me>\begin{aligned}
x_0 &amp; = &amp;a\\
x_1 &amp; = &amp;a+\Delta x\\
\ &amp; \vdots &amp; \\
x_i &amp; = &amp; a + i\Delta x\\
\ &amp; \vdots &amp; \\
x_n &amp; = &amp; b.\\
\end{aligned}</me> The midpoints of each sub-interval are given by <m>m_i = \frac{x_i+x_{i+1}}{2}</m>.
	</p>

